item.title: About
item.description: I am a Research Assistant at the NBER for Princeton’s Woodrow Wilson School professor Christopher Neilson. My academic interests lie within the fields of education, public policy and data analysis. Interests beyond academia include anything computers, music, politics (who doesn’t), and the natural sciences in general. Prior to this current position I completed a B.A. in Economics at Southern Connecticut State University, graduating in Fall 2016. Throughout my undergraduate degree I worked at a small local company as a business analyst.
